---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Exam Strategy | Economic Policy Study Site">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Final weeks</p>
    <h1>Exam Strategy</h1>
    <p>
      A strong exam answer in this course usually does two things well: it states the economic logic clearly and it
      uses the right equations or theoretical structure without skipping the reasoning that connects them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid section">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What high-scoring preparation looks like</h2>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Know the intuition and the formal object for every major topic.</li>
        <li>Practice moving from shock description to variable responses without hesitation.</li>
        <li>Train yourself to distinguish assumptions, mechanisms, and conclusions in writing.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>What weak preparation looks like</h2>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Recognizing equations but not being able to explain where they come from.</li>
        <li>Knowing labels like “commitment” or “Ricardian equivalence” without being able to use them in an argument.</li>
        <li>Doing too little timed practice before the exam week.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

